=== Lesson 25-1 (Introduction) ===

 {"type":"h3","text":"Germaine's Guide to RC Inference Questions"}
 {"type":"paragraph","text":"Inference questions ask you to identify a statement that is **very likely to be true**...The most important mental model is to check for evidential backing: **\"Because this text in the passage is true, I know this answer is true.\"**"}

{ "type": "diff-note", "text": "The 'Because this text is true, I know this answer is true' mental model is the best single teaching sentence in the module. Preserve and emphasize it.", "variant": "comment" }

